title: The Circus
overview: The Tramp finds work and the girl of his dreams at a circus.

title: The Apartment
overview: A man tries to rise in his company by letting its executives use his apartment for trysts, but complications and a romance of his own ensue.

title: The Artist
overview: An egomaniacal film star develops a relationship with a young dancer against the backdrop of Hollywood's silent era.

title: The Sandlot
overview: In the summer of 1962, a new kid in town is taken under the wing of a young baseball prodigy and his rowdy team, resulting in many adventures.

title: The Station Agent
overview: When his only friend dies, a man born with dwarfism moves to rural New Jersey to live a life of solitude, only to meet a chatty hot dog vendor and a woman dealing with her own personal loss.

title: The Quiet Man
overview: A retired American boxer returns to the village of his birth in Ireland, where he falls for a spirited redhead whose brother is contemptuous of their union.

title: The Breakfast Club
overview: Five high school students meet in Saturday detention and discover how they have a lot more in common than they thought.

title: The Shop Around the Corner
overview: Two employees at a gift shop can barely stand each other, without realizing that they are falling in love through the post as each other's anonymous pen pal.

title: The Long Goodbye
overview: Private investigator Philip Marlowe helps a friend out of a jam, but in doing so gets implicated in his wife's murder.

title: The Kid
overview: The Tramp cares for an abandoned child, but events put that relationship in jeopardy.

title: The Royal Tenenbaums
overview: The eccentric members of a dysfunctional family reluctantly gather under the same roof for various reasons.

title: My Cousin Vinny
overview: Two New Yorkers accused of murder in rural Alabama while on their way back to college call in the help of one of their cousins, a loudmouth lawyer with no trial experience.

title: The Ladykillers
overview: Five oddball criminals planning a bank robbery rent rooms on a cul-de-sac from an octogenarian widow under the pretext that they are classical musicians.

title: The Graduate
overview: A disillusioned college graduate finds himself torn between his older lover and her daughter.

title: The Sting
overview: Two grifters team up to pull off the ultimate con.

title: The Big Lebowski
overview: Jeff "The Dude" Lebowski, mistaken for a millionaire of the same name, seeks restitution for his ruined rug and enlists his bowling buddies to help get it.

title: The Philadelphia Story
overview: When a rich woman's ex-husband and a tabloid-type reporter turn up just before her planned remarriage, she begins to learn the truth about herself.

title: The Muppet Christmas Carol
overview: The Muppet characters tell their version of the classic tale of an old and bitter miser's redemption on Christmas Eve.

title: The Odd Couple
overview: Two friends try sharing an apartment, but their ideas of housekeeping and lifestyles are as different as night and day.

title: The Thin Man
overview: Former detective Nick Charles and his wealthy wife Nora investigate a murder case, mostly for the fun of it.
